EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO STATE AFFAIRS AND GOVERNMENT-- CORRECTIONS DEPARTMENT
***
1 This act would repeal provisions which allow the department of corrections to charge
2 inmates for phone calls and would require the department of corrections to provide free
3 communication services to inmates and juveniles held in residential placement or detention centers.
4 This act also would require that those facilities provide in-person contact visits.
5 This act would take effect upon passage.
